info.name: IDX API 1.4.0 Test Runner
info.description:
IDX Broker API calls in version 1.4.0

Required:
* Environment variable url
* Environment variable for request headers
* Environment variable partner key
* Client account with at least one featured listing

Tests are in this order as variables such as listing ID and approved MLS are passed to subsequent API calls.

exec: /** Check status code is under 300 if so run tests
* The following are standard tests to be preformed on all endpoints.
* Some tests will only run if status is below 300
// rerport the status code is in the 200s
// get response body length for test
// tests when code is 200 and body lenth greater than 0
// set variable of body legnth and assume true
// test body length when code is 204. Must be 0
//if body legnth is 0 then set variable to true
tests["Retun Length is correct for http code"] = bodyLength;
tests["Does NOT contain text \"PHP Warning\""] = phpWarn;
//run test that response was under 30 seconds
tests["Response time is under than 30 sec"] = responseTime < 30000;

request.description:
This method provides all of the IDX IDs and names for all of the paperwork approved MLSs on the client's account.

Note: This method was previously camelcased as "approvedMLS" but was made lower case to fit the API naming convention. Calls to "approvedMLS" will be forwarded to "approvedmls" and "approvedMLS" is listed as deprecated in the method list.
